Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan's three prime fast bowlers are unfit, and Shadab Khan's form has been poor.
Netherlands' last 50-over game was in the World Cup Qualifier three months ago, with both warm-up games being rain-affected.
Shadab Khan's place in the starting lineup might be determined by his performance against the Netherlands.
Haris Rauf asked after Bas de Leede's health after a bouncer from the bowler had given him a concussion and a nasty cut under the eye in the last match between the two sides.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan are 26 runs away from becoming the first active Pakistan batter to make 500 ODI World Cup runs.
Pakistan have lost the first World Cup match at the last two tournaments, and four of the last five.
Netherlands have won just two of their 15 World Cup matches, their last success coming in 2007 against Scotland.
